article_text:
NEW YORK—Oil prices managed a gain Thursday after weekly inventory data showed bigger-than-expected drops in crude and gasoline supplies.

Light, sweet oil for July delivery settled up 17 cents, or 0.3%, at $57.68 a barrel on the New York Mercantile...
